g pot 4-5 in. deep)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"6 tbsp baking soda"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"coarse salt, to taste"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"mustard, to serve"}],"nutrition":["per 1","874 kJ \/ 209 kcal","7 g","41 g","2 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["To reheat: place each pretzel on a piece of foil large enough to completely wrap it. Add about 1 tbsp water per pretzel then wrap as tightly as possible. Set oven to 250°F and reheat approximately 20 minutes.","To freeze: place baked pretzels on a baking sheet and freeze for approximately an hour. Once the pretzels are frozen, store in a freezer bag or container until you are ready to heat &amp; eat. To reheat your pretzels – Preheat oven to 350°. Place pretzels on a baking sheet and bake for about 4-6 minutes."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","55m","12 pieces"]}